# Component primitives (avoid duplicated sections)

Tailwind utilities belong in markup for one-offs. When the same **structure + classes** appear in more than one place, extract a React component. Do not copy-paste section wrappers across pages.

This pairs with `css-layout.mdc` (flex/grid, responsive rules). That rule covers *how* to lay out; this rule covers *where* layout lives.

Sources: [Tailwind: Extracting components](https://tailwindcss.com/docs/reusing-styles#extracting-components), [Tailwind: Avoiding premature abstraction](https://tailwindcss.com/docs/utility-first).

## When to extract vs keep inline

| Keep utilities inline | Extract a component |
|-----------------------|---------------------|
| Unique page layout used once | Same wrapper appears on 2+ pages or 2+ times on one page |
| Small tweak on a single element | Card/panel shell, stat block, form field row, toolbar row |
| DaisyUI defaults with no extra structure | Title + body + actions pattern (settings sections, account cards) |

**Do not** create `@apply` CSS classes for UI sections. Prefer a component with utilities inside it. Reserve `@apply` for global base styles (see `index.css`).

**Do not** extract too early: a one-off onboarding wizard step can stay inline. Extract when you copy the pattern or expect to reuse it.

## Project patterns to centralize

These strings are duplicated today. Use or add primitives in `src/components/` instead of re-declaring them:

| Pattern | Repeated as | Prefer |
|---------|-------------|--------|
| Panel / section card | `card bg-base-200 border border-eve-border` (+ `card-body`, `card-title`) | `Panel` or `SectionCard` with `title`, `children`, optional `actions`, `className` |
| Stat tile | `stat bg-base-200 rounded-lg border border-eve-border` | `StatCard` with `label`, `value`, optional `description` |
| Page title row | inline flex header | existing `PageHeader` in `Layout.tsx` |
| Loading / empty | spinner block | existing `LoadingState` |
| Form label + control | `label.form-control` + `span.label-text` | extend `FormFieldLabel` or add `FormField` wrapper with a `control` slot |
| Filter / toolbar row | `flex flex-wrap gap-2` + buttons | `Toolbar` or page-local subcomponent when the row is non-trivial |

Before adding a new page section, search the codebase for an existing primitive or the same class combo.

## How to write a primitive

1. **Single source of truth** for the class string inside the component file.
2. **`className` prop** on the outer element for page-specific spacing (`mb-6`, `lg:col-span-2`). Merge with a template literal or add `cn()` later if overrides get messy.
3. **Semantic props** over layout props when possible: `title`, `compact`, `actions`, not `marginBottom={6}`.
4. **Slots via `children`** for body content; optional `header`/`footer` only when the pattern repeats.
5. **Colocate** in `src/components/` (feature-specific subcomponents stay next to their page until reused).

```tsx
// ❌ Duplicated on every settings section
<section className="card bg-base-200 border border-eve-border">
  <div className="card-body">
    <h2 className="card-title text-base">{title}</h2>
    {children}
  </div>
</section>

// ✅ One component, many pages
export function Panel({ title, children, className, actions }: PanelProps) {
  return (
    <section className={`card bg-base-200 border border-eve-border ${className ?? ''}`}>
      <div className="card-body">
        <div className="flex items-center justify-between gap-2">
          <h2 className="card-title text-base">{title}</h2>
          {actions}
        </div>
        {children}
      </div>
    </section>
  )
}
```

## Variants

Start with inline classes and optional props (`size="sm"`, `compact`). Add `class-variance-authority` or `tailwind-variants` only when a primitive grows multiple variants (button-like complexity). This project does not use them yet; avoid new dependencies for a two-option prop.

## File organization

- **Shared UI primitives**: `src/components/Panel.tsx`, `StatCard.tsx`, etc.
- **Page-only structure**: extract a named subcomponent in the same file (`AccountsPage.tsx` → `CharacterCard`) when the block is large but not reused elsewhere yet.
- **Do not** put new layout primitives in `index.css` or duplicate them in every page file.

## Before finishing

- [ ] No new copy of `card bg-base-200 border border-eve-border` (or other repeated shell) without checking for an existing primitive
- [ ] Page uses `PageHeader`, `LoadingState`, and shared form/panel components where they fit
- [ ] Layout/responsive classes still follow `css-layout.mdc`
- [ ] One-off markup stays inline; shared markup lives in `src/components/`
